{{Quote|The real way to harm an Ewok is through his Soul Tree. Once you destroy an Ewok's Soul Tree, you destroy his will to live.|[[Murgoob]], Dulok oracle|<ref name="Wicket's Wagon">{{Ewoks|Wicket's Wagon}}</ref>}}
A '''Soul Tree''',<ref name="Cries">{{Ewoks|The Cries of the Trees}}</ref> also known as a '''birth-tree''',<ref name="Teebo">''[[The Adventures of Teebo: A Tale of Magic and Suspense]]''</ref> was a sacred tree planted in the forest of the [[Moon/Legends|moon]] of [[Endor/Legends|Endor]] at the time of an [[Ewok/Legends|Ewok's]] birth. The Ewok was thought to be spiritually connected to the tree, meaning that the condition of the tree hinted at the health or character of the Ewok to which it was bound. Upon the Ewok's death, his or her hood was attached to the Soul Tree's trunk, and the Ewok's spirit was thought to take up residence in the totem tree. At least one Ewok [[Force ghost/Legends|spirit]] is known to have stayed with its Soul Tree after death, protecting it from harm, that of [[Erpham Warrick]].

Due to their connection to the ancients, the Soul Trees as a whole were thought to be a source of power for Ewok [[Shaman/Legends|shamans]]. These holy Ewoks often tried to make contact with the ancestors and to draw upon their power through the medium of the Soul Trees. Shamans could be very secretive about these rituals.

Unfortunately, the enemies of Ewoks are well aware of the strategic value destroying the soul trees to deeply traumatize the species and make them easily conquerable. To that end to defeat the Ewoks of [[Bright Tree Village/Legends|Bright Tree Village]], [[Morag]] the [[Tulgah/Legends|Tulgah]] witch tried to destroy their Soul Trees by burning them with enslaved [[Wistie/Legends|Wisties]]. The plan was thwarted when [[Wicket Wystri Warrick/Legends|Wicket Wystri Warrick]] and his friends doused the trees in magical foam. The second major chronicled attempt was when the Duloks captured Erpham Warrick's [[Ewok battle wagon]] rebuilt by Wicket to ram down the soul trees. The young Ewok again thwarted this attempt by collapsing the wagon before it could cause significant damage.

[[Kaink/Legends|Kaink]] was the guardian of Bright Tree Village's Soul Trees.

==Behind the scenes==
{{Quote|The Ewoks have a sort of spiritual bond with their trees – all having to do with The Force and its various manifestations throughout the universe.|[[Paul Dini]]|<ref name="RFS">{{WebCite|url=http://radiofreesacramento.com/?p=321|text=From JEDI to Television: The Saga of the EWOKS and DROIDS Adventure Hour – Part I|author=Dennis Post|date=2015-09-07|archivedate=20210421171733 }}</ref>}}
Soul Trees were created by [[Joe Johnston]] for his book ''[[The Adventures of Teebo: A Tale of Magic and Suspense]]''.

